    <item>
      <title>Potions vs Beastlords</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=beastlordbalance&amp;message.id=3290#M3290</link>
      <description>It's getting a bit rediculous.  Potions are doing more than beastlord spells and abilities.  Stacking between classes aside, lets just look at the pure effects of the potions vs our spells.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Let's start with one of the simplest ones:&lt;br&gt;vender haste potion: &lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=6949" target=_blank&gt;http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=6949&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;beastlord spell: &lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=171" target=_blank&gt;http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=171&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;Both are 50% haste.  The potion lasts nearly twice as long.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Another simple case:&lt;br&gt;vender direct heal potion: &lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=6929" target=_blank&gt;http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=6929&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;best beastlord heal spell: &lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=5528" target=_blank&gt;http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=5528&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;The potion heals "1543 to 1750 (random)", beastlord heal heals 1165.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Mana regen? Well there too:&lt;br&gt;vender mana regen potion: &lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=6959" target=_blank&gt;http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=6959&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;spiritual ascendance: &lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=5537" target=_blank&gt;http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=5537&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our spell adds 10 mana per tick, the potion adds 14.&lt;br&gt;If you want to throw in using the best Perfection of Spirit aa everytime it pops, that would basically add another 4.4 mana per tick.  That makes the figures about even.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Heal over time?  For that we have two things: Perfection of Spirit and Growl of the Panther (self-only + pet).&lt;br&gt;vender heal-over-time: &lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=6919" target=_blank&gt;http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=6919&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;purrfection3: &lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=5856" target=_blank&gt;http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=5856&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;growl: &lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=6672" target=_blank&gt;http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=6672&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;The potion adds "635 to 769 (random) per tick" (average would be 702).  Our aa ability? 267.  Growl adds 150 to pet and us.  Even if you added both of ours together and counted growl as double, it still heals less per tick than a vender-sold potion.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;It's just a bit absurd that we are out-classed by vender sold potions.  I don't think the potions were a bad idea, in fact I use many of them myself.  There are some cases where what they add might have been pushing it, but overall I'd not say they're too strong.  So that pretty much leaves the state of our spells in general (and perfection of spirit) as the part that's lacking here.</description>
